As I’m finishing up my US Open this year and typing this, I want everybody to know that this tournament is no joke. 
I have had success in it and I’ve done very poor as well. 
It takes a true test of patience, it takes a lot of hard work and dedication, and a test of versatility. 
I made alot of mistakes on all 3 of those and that is why I’ll be watching the rest of the tournament from the sideline. 
Am I upset with my performance? Yes. 
Does this mean I should give up? No. 
Failure is not the opposite of success. It is part of success. 
Moving on from this knowing I’ll push myself to do even better for the next tournament. 
Springfield next week. ❤️

#USOpen #Columbia300 #VISE #Coolwick #BowlerX #TeamVirtue #familytiesbowling #grind #neverbackdown

Everybody ask what’s life like on Tour?
What it’s like week in and week out? 

You see all the TV shows and success bowlers have week in and week out and think that it’s the best life you can have. 

People don’t see the sacrifices you make when you take all the time to make a commitment to tour. Not only do you have to stay committed to the tour season, you have to leave home for months at a time, leaving behind family and friends, and you live out of a suitcase months at a time. 

Commitment is the biggest key to going out and doing the tour life. 
The support we get from you fans is our support away from home. We are all thankful for you. ❤️

Hey everybody. It’s been awhile since I have made a post in regards to any bowling. Unfortunately I had a an injury in my thigh that I never let fully heal and because of that, I’m giving it time to get the proper rest. It’s a hard decision because I unfortunately had to withdraw from a handful of great tournaments, including the Pan American Games in Chile at the end of the month. A red hot Aj Johnson is taking my place to bowl with Brandon Bonta on the guys side. Along with them representing the girls is Breanna Clemmer and Jordan Richard. It’s one of the more difficult decisions I’ve had to make but health always comes first. I can assure you they will represent 🇺🇸 very well. Thank you all for the support and the goal is to come back stronger than ever. ❤️
